1 AN ACT concerning water; relating to the certification of operators of
2 water supply systems and wastewater treatment facilities; requiring fees
3 for operator certification examinations to not exceed the cost of such
4 examinations; eliminating the ability of the secretary of health and
5 environment to certify operators through a correspondence course
6 rather than classroom instruction; amending K.S.A. 65-4513 and
7 repealing the existing section; also repealing K.S.A. 65-4506.
8
9 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
10 Section 1. K.S.A. 65-4513 is hereby amended to read as follows: 65-
11 4513. The secretary shall establish a reasonable schedule of fees but in no
12 case shall an individual operator examination fee exceed twenty-five
13 dollars ($25) in any one year the cost of an individual operator
14 certification exam.
15 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 65-4506 and 65-4513 are hereby repealed.
16 Sec. 3. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
17 publication in the statute book.

